	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Cave</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From The Cataclysm: Dark Days Ahead Wiki</div>
		<div id="contentSub"><div class="mw-revision"><div id="mw-revision-info">Revision as of 15:24, 12 May 2020 by <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/User:Soyweiser" class="mw-userlink" title="User:Soyweiser"><bdi>Soyweiser</bdi></a> <span class="mw-usertoollinks">(<a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/User_talk:Soyweiser" class="mw-usertoollinks-talk" title="User talk:Soyweiser">talk</a> | <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Special:Contributions/Soyweiser" class="mw-usertoollinks-contribs" title="Special:Contributions/Soyweiser">contribs</a>)</span></div><div id="mw-revision-nav">(<a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Cave&amp;diff=prev&amp;oldid=35426" title="Cave">diff</a>) <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Cave&amp;direction=prev&amp;oldid=35426" title="Cave">← Older revision</a> | Latest revision (diff) | Newer revision → (diff)</div></div></div>
		
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><br />
</p>
<table class="infobox" cellspacing="5" style="width: 22em; text-align: left; font-size: 88%; line-height: 1.5em; width: 150px;">
<caption>
</caption>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="" colspan="2" style="font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; text-align:center;"><span style="font: 1em FixedSys, monospace; color:SaddleBrown; background:black;">C</span> cave
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th style="">See Cost
</th>
<td class="" style="width: 70%;">2
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th style="">Extras
</th>
<td class="" style="width: 70%;">field
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>A <a class="mw-selflink selflink">cave</a> is a rocky outcrop on the surface that leads to a small underground area.  Here you can fight with a <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Black_bear" title="Black bear">bear</a> or two, or a <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Wolf_(monster)" title="Wolf (monster)">wolf</a>, for <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Comestibles" title="Comestibles">food</a>.  A cave might also be a hermit cave, in which case it will contain a corpse and some rare items. Bring a lighting source to scare <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Bat" title="Bat">bats</a>.
</p><p>With a one-third chance, any cave might turn into a <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Rat_cave" title="Rat cave">rat cave</a> on generation.  In this case, it will have a <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Rat_cave" title="Rat cave">second level</a> and will be filled with <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Sewer_rat" title="Sewer rat">sewer rats</a> and a boss.
</p><p>The underground part of caves can be often overridden by <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Sewer" title="Sewer">sewers</a> or <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Subway" title="Subway">subway</a> that happen to intersect it.  In these cases, the downslope will likely end abruptly in a sheer drop, offering you the opportunity to jump, glide, or rappel down, depending on the assets available to you.
</p><p>Caves can be somewhat decent places to live if you can get rid of what creatures are down there, and if you have a <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Rollmat" title="Rollmat">rollmat</a> or other items that provide bedding, if you are a <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Troglobite" title="Troglobite">troglobite</a> character, even better, as <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Subterranean_Fortitude" title="Subterranean Fortitude">Subterranean Fortitude</a> can allow the player to sleep better on the hard rock floors of the cave without the need for a bed..
</p>
